    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_EstimatedMeterReadingsReport",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to generate a report of estimated meter readings for utility accounts. It filters data based on the energy type and retrieves information about accounts that have not had a meter reading for at least one month. The procedure uses a common table expression (CTE) to gather and process data from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Published.TemporalAccountMeterLevelRawDataForCurrentPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table, joining it with the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.EnergyDeliveryType",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table to include energy delivery type descriptions. The final result set includes details such as agency name, billing period, facility address, utility company, account number, meter number, and the number of months since the last meter reading."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level is considered medium due to the use of a CTE, multiple table joins, and conditional logic for filtering based on the input parameter. The procedure also involves string manipulation and conditional expressions, which add to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
